{
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, the approximation β = -∇ϕ = -α will lead to the persistence of high-order terms in the residual B-modes power spectrum, thereby degrading its performance.However, in our methodology, we employ an iterative approach instead of relying on the approximation.",
    "This iterative method effectively incorporates the second-order term ∇α(n) • β(n) into β. Consequently, it ensures that the second-order lensing effect is properly accounted for in the remapped field.",
    "As a result, the second terms in the residual B-modes power spectrum are canceled out, leading to comparable performance with the gradient order template method.",
    "For more details, please refer to [29].In terms of implementation efficiency, the non-perturbative template method stands out as the fastest.",
    "This is because we only need use Lenspyx to remap the lensed maps again with ϕ map, which is a relatively quick process."
  ]
}